SHDL
====

Scheme Hardware Description Language (SHDL).


Example
-------

> (define a (make-wire))
> (define b (make-wire))
> (define c-in (make-wire))
> (define s (make-wire))
> (define c-out (make-wire))
> (full-adder a b c-in s c-out)
ok
> (set-signal! a 1)
done
> (set-signal! b 1)
done
> (propagate)
done
> (get-signal s)
0
> (get-signal c-out)
1


References
----------

- Structure and Interpretation of Computer Programs (SICP),
  Harold Abelson, Gerald Jay Sussman, Julie Sussman
